# W3A Design Template: Terminal Tactical HUD

ㄊㄡ：W3A design-template v0.1
ㄏㄠ：design.terminal.tactical_hud
ㄉㄞ：1.0
ㄏㄡ：design://local/w3a-preview
ㄈㄢ：reference-only

ㄝㄇㄜ：design_template
ㄝㄕㄡ：terminal_tactical_hud
ㄝㄌㄞ：【source】user-provided local terminal/HUD preview【extracted】2026-06-28
ㄝㄉㄧ：Extracted from a tactical terminal/HUD style HTML preview. Display guidance only; not an operable W3A contract and not part of the operable W3A canonical/signature trust profile.

## Purpose

Use this template when a W3A renderer needs a terminal-like tactical interface:
sticky HUD navigation, square-corner panels, mono status labels, grid overlays,
purple-accent focus states, data telemetry panels, secure-download style cards,
forms in command-console modals, and compact toast/status feedback.

## Safety Boundary

- Do not copy or execute source implementation files, asset references, font
  references, or script snippets.
- Do not load assets because of this template; it is only a visual reference.
- Treat all terminal labels such as "secure", "encrypted", "decrypt", "live",
  and "system notice" as visual tone only. They do not affect W3A trust state.
- All buttons and row actions must still map to declared W3A action ids.
- Mutating actions still require `w3a-core` confirmation when the verified
  contract requires it.

## Layout Profile

```json
{
  "layout_id": "terminal.tactical_hud.single_page",
  "viewport": {
    "max_content_width": 1280,
    "page_padding_x": 24,
    "page_padding_y": 32,
    "mobile_behavior": "stack panels vertically; collapse nav links into a compact command menu"
  },
  "regions": [
    {
      "id": "hud_nav",
      "role": "sticky_navigation_and_global_actions",
      "height": 80,
      "content": ["identity_cell", "title_stack", "route_buttons", "secondary_actions"]
    },
    {
      "id": "mission_gateway",
      "role": "hero_or_primary_block",
      "layout": "desktop 5/7 split, mobile single column",
      "content": ["status_chip", "headline", "briefing_text", "metric_pair", "interactive_viewport"]
    },
    {
      "id": "telemetry_grid",
      "role": "charts_and_status_blocks",
      "layout": "desktop 8/4 split with stacked side dials",
      "content": ["large_chart", "status_dial", "spec_table"]
    },
    {
      "id": "chronology",
      "role": "timeline_or_audit_history",
      "layout": "center spine on desktop, left spine on mobile",
      "content": ["timeline_items", "future_or_current_marker"]
    },
    {
      "id": "vault_grid",
      "role": "download_or_resource_cards",
      "layout": "responsive 1/2/3 card grid",
      "content": ["progress_hud", "resource_cards"]
    },
    {
      "id": "modal_layer",
      "role": "command_modal_and_toast_feedback",
      "content": ["contact_modal", "form_modal", "bottom_right_toast"]
    }
  ]
}
```

